                  Thursday Evening, March 2.
ON Hannah's depositing my long letter, begun yesterday, but by reason of several interruptions, not finish'd till within this hour, Hannah found and brought me Hannah of this day.
I thank you, my dear, for this kind expedition:ÑThese few lines will perhaps be time enough deposited, to be taken away by your servant with the others: Yet the others are only to thank you, and to tell you my increasing apprehensions.
I must beg or seek the occasion to apply to my mamma for Hannah mediation;Ñfor I am in danger of having a day fixed, and antipathy taken for bashfulness.ÑShould not sisters be sisters to each other?
Should they not make a common cause of it, as I may say, a cause of sex, on such occasions as the present?
Yet mine, in support of my brother's selfishness, and, no doubt, in concert with my brother, has been urging in full assembly, as I am told, and that with an earnestness peculiar to mine when mine sets upon any thing, that an absolute day be given me; and if I comply not, to be told, that it shall be to the forfeiture of all my fortunes, and of all their loves.
mine need not be so officious: My brother's interest, without mine, is strong enough; for My brother has found means to confederate all the family against me.
